<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib special">201. Leland, Nita. Exploring Color: How to Use and Control Colorin Your Paintings. Cincinnati: North Light, 1985. 192 pp. Index, bibl., glossary, B/W illus., color illus. ISBN 0-89134-111-0. </p><p class="annot">Directed at artists, this book begins with a brief overview of colortheory and practice in art. After summarizing pigments and techniques, watercolorist Nita Leland discusses the characteristics of color and then applies this information to pigments. Through a series of 87 exercises she helps the reader explore color design, including composition, harmonies and contrasts, and expression. Hundreds of color illustrations complement the clearly written text. This is a useful resource applicable to many paint mediums in addition to watercolor.</p></div>
